channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: 'Full-Blown Freakout,' Democrats Are Having a Panic Attack Over Joe Biden's Electoral Prospects
Texas Republican primary runoffs feature political revenge, Trump as key factors
item.description: Former President Trump, Texas Gov. Greg Abbott and AG Ken Paxton are key players in Republican primary runoff elections, while Rep. Tony Gonzales fights for political survival.

item.title: Trump Jury to Hear Closing Arguments Tuesday Before Deliberations
item.description: New York prosecutors and Donald Trump's lawyers make their closing arguments at his legal expenses Tuesday in a final bid to influence the 12 jurors who decide whether he will become the first U.S. president past or present convicted of a crime.

item.title: Richard Dreyfuss' Remarks at 'Jaws' Screening Incite Firestorm and Question As to What He Actually Said
Explained: Clarence Thomas’ split with conservatives to save 'Elizabeth Warren's baby'
item.description: Legal experts explain why Justice Clarence Thomas split from his conservative colleagues to save the controversial CFPB in latest Supreme Court decision.

item.title: Texas Runoff Elections Pivotal For Abbott, Paxton
item.description: Runoff elections Tuesday in Texas could go a long way in helping Gov. Greg Abbott and Attorney General Ken Paxton, both Republicans, put the political careers of several GOP adversaries out of business.

item.title: Sleeping With the Enemy: Biden Warns European Allies Not to Rebuke Iran's Nuclear Program
Indiana Republican accuses Dem challenger of abandoning constituents, joining 'DC political machine'
item.description: Rep. Frank Mrvan, D-Ind., has abandoned his constituents and joined the "D.C. political machine" after joining Congress three years ago, according to his GOP challenger.

item.title: N.C. County Sued to Remove 'Faithful Slaves' Monument
item.description: A group of residents in a small North Carolina county filed a federal lawsuit to remove a Confederate-era monument that pays tribute to "our faithful slaves."

item.title: Co-Owning a Home Probably a Bad Idea for Most
NY v. Trump: Closing arguments to begin as Merchan skirts decision on motion to dismiss
item.description: The jury is expected to return Tuesday to hear closing arguments in the unprecedented criminal case against former President Trump.

item.title: Pat Fallon to Newsmax: Joe Biden Would Pardon Hunter
item.description: First son Hunter Biden never will serve jail time even if he's found guilty of gun charges, Rep. Pat Fallon, R-Texas, told Newsmax on Monday night.

item.title: Memorial Day Through the Eyes of a Green Beret Wife
Biden honors late son Beau in somber Memorial Day message: ‘The hurt is still real’
item.description: President Biden on Monday invoked the memory of his late son, Iraq War veteran Beau Biden, while addressing an audience at Arlington National Cemetery for a Memorial Day ceremony.

item.title: 'Squad' Reps Omar, Bush Bashed for Memorial Day Gaffe
item.description: A pair of far left members of "the Squad" were pulverized in the court of public opinion on Monday after confusing Memorial Day with Veterans Day, a gaffe that forced them to delete and then repost accurate sentiments to social media.
